Read mode:=
It will read the content from the file
eg: myfile=open("myfile.txt","r")
    myfile.read()
write mode:=
 It will write the content to the file
eg:myfile=open("myfile.txt","w")

myfile.write()

Append mode:=
 it will append the content to the file..

Calculator with python language


 def user():
 x=int(input ("Enterthe value of x:"))
 y=int(input("Enter the value of y:"))
 i=int(input("enter i"))
 a=0
 if i==1:
    a=x+y
    print("Addition of two numbers",a)
    return a
 elif i==2:
    a=x-y
    print("Subtraction of two numbers",a)
    return a
 elif i==3:
   a=x*y
   print("Multiplication of two numbers",a)
   return a
 elif i==4:
   a=x/y
   print("Division of two numbers",a)
   return a
 else:
      print("invalid")
      return a
      

b=user()
myfile=open("myfile.txt","w")
rec=str(b)+'\n'
myfile.write(rec)
print(myfile)
myfile.close()
